creator: Jean-Henri Fabre
description:
LibriVox recording of The Life of the Fly, With Which are Interspersed Some Chapters of Autobiography by Jean-Henri Fabre. (Translated by Alexander Teixeira de Mattos.)
Read in English by Bellona Times
The title tells all, along with other observations on insect life from the famed accidental entomologist of 19th Century France.. - Summary by BellonaTimes
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
subject: librivox; audiobooks;science; insects; chemistry; fly
